te foods available, providing high-quality protein, essential fats, and a full spectrum of vitamins and minerals that support brain function, muscle health, and metabolic stability."},{name:"Salmon",text:"Salmon delivers omega-3 fatty acids, protein, and vitamin D in a form the body readily absorbs. These nutrients support heart health, reduce inflammation, and promote cognitive function."},{name:"Chicken",text:"Chicken provides lean, complete protein essential for muscle maintenance and repair. It's versatile, affordable, and easily prepared as part of a whole-food eating pattern."},{name:"Beef",text:"Beef supplies iron, zinc, B12, and complete protein in highly bioavailable forms. Grass-fed options provide additional omega-3s and conjugated linoleic acid."},{name:"Cheese",text:"Cheese concentrates the nutrients of milk—protein, calcium, and fat-soluble vitamins—into a satisfying food that supports bone health and provides sustained energy."},{name:"Butter",text:"Butter from grass-fed sources provides fat-soluble vitamins A, D, E, and K2, along with beneficial fatty acids that support nutrient absorption and metabolic health."}]},"fruits-vegetables":{title:"Vegetables & Fruits",description:"Vegetables and fruits are essential to real food nutrition. Eat a wide variety of whole, colorful, nutrient-dense vegetables and fruits in their original form, prioritizing freshness and minimal processing.",servings:[{label:"Vegetables:",text:"3 servings per day."},{label:"Fruits:",text:"2 servings per day."}],items:[{name:"Carrots",text:"Carrots are a nutrient-dense vegetable rich in beta-carotene, which the body converts to vitamin A to support vision, immune function, and skin health."},{name:"Lettuce",text:"Lettuce is a hydrating, low-calorie vegetable that adds volume, crunch, and freshness to meals. It provides fiber, folate, and vitamin K."},{name:"Broccoli",text:"Broccoli is rich in fiber, vitamin C, vitamin K, and protective plant compounds that support immune and metabolic health."},{name:"Tomatoes",text:"Tomatoes are a whole-food source of vitamin C, potassium, and lycopene, a plant compound linked to heart and metabolic health."},{name:"Apples",text:"Apples provide fiber, vitamin C, and natural plant compounds that support gut and metabolic health."},{name:"Bananas",text:"Bananas offer potassium, vitamin B6, and natural sugars that provide quick energy while supporting muscle and nerve function."}]},"whole-grains":{title:"Whole Grains",description:"Whole grains are encouraged. Refined carbohydrates are not. Prioritize fiber-rich whole grains and significantly reduce the consumption of highly processed, refined carbohydrates that displace real nourishment.",servings:[{label:"Target:",text:"2–4 servings per day."}],items:[{name:"Oats",text:"Oats are a fiber-rich whole grain that supports heart health and provides sustained energy through their complex carbohydrates and beta-glucan fiber."},{name:"Brown Rice",text:"Brown rice retains its bran and germ, providing fiber, B vitamins, and minerals that white rice lacks. It's a versatile base for balanced meals."},{name:"Whole Wheat",text:"Whole wheat bread and pasta made from 100% whole grain flour provide fiber and nutrients stripped from refined versions."},{name:"Quinoa",text:"Quinoa is a complete protein source among grains, providing all essential amino acids along with fiber, iron, and magnesium."}]}},e8=[{row:2,name:"Bread",image:"/images/pyramid/bread.webp",width:816,height:612,x:249,y:298,x2:286,y2:293,x3:291,scale1:.112,scale2:.136},{row:2,name:"Bowl Oats",image:"/images/pyramid/bowl-oats.webp",width:520,height:416,x:240,y:343,x2:251,y2:336.5,x3:256,scale1:.112,scale2:.14},{row:1,name:"Oats",image:"/images/pyramid/oats.webp",width:512,height:432,x:231,y:378,x2:199,y2:370,x3:204,scale1:.118,scale2:.14}],e9=[{row:3,name:"Broccoli",image:"/images/pyramid/broccoli.webp",width:890,height:705,x:281,y:62,x2:283,y2:204,x3:32.2,y3:102.4,scale1:.1,scale2:.084,z1:0,z2:-1},{row:3,name: