/div><div class="dga_card__W4f_X" style="z-index:1"><img data-food="Chicken" src="images/pyramid/chicken.webp" alt="Chicken" style="opacity:0;transform:none"/></div></div><p class="dga_h2_food___9BYt" style="opacity:0;transform:translateX(-180px) scale(0.8)">Salmon</p></div><footer class="dga_footer__qYjWA"><div class="dga_container__KeUzb"><span class="dga_nds_text__RzD_v">Designed &amp; Engineered in D.C. by<!-- --> <a rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" href="https://ndstudio.gov/">National Design Studio</a></span></div></footer></section></div><!--$--><!--/$--><section aria-label="Notifications alt+T" tabindex="-1" aria-live="polite" aria-relevant="additions text" aria-atomic="false"></section><script src="_next/static/chunks/webpack-93bee8f9c6c956fd.js" id="_R_" async=""></script><script>(self.__next_f=self.__next_f||[]).push([0])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"1:\"$Sreact.fragment\"\n6:I[338,[],\"\"]\n:HL[\"/_next/static/css/42ea1df623d2f729.css\",\"style\"]\n:HL[\"/_next/static/css/5fe99a30101789d7.css\",\"style\"]\n2:Ta53,"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the New Pyramid?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The New Pyramid is a simple guide designed to help Americans eat real, whole foods more consistently. It prioritizes nutrient-dense foods and reduces reliance on highly processed products, using modern nutrition science to support everyday health.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does “Eat Real Food” mean?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Eating real food means choosing foods that are whole or minimally processed and recognizable as food. These foods are prepared with few ingredients and without added sugars, industrial oils, artificial flavors, or preservatives.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Why does the New Pyramid emphasize protein and vegetables?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Protein and vegetables form the foundation of real food meals. Together, they support muscle health, metabolic function, gut health, and stable energy while naturally crowding out highly processed foods.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are fats part of eating real foods?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes. Healthy fats are a natural part of real foods such as meat, seafood, dairy, nuts, olives, and avocados. These fats support brain health, hormone function, and nutrient absorption when consumed in their natural forms.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How does the New Pyramid address added sugars?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Added sugars are not part of eating real foods and are not recommended. The New Pyramid encourages avoiding added sugars entirely, especially for children, while allowing naturally occurring sugars found in whole fruits and plain dairy.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where do grains fit in the New Pyramid?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Grains can be part of a real food diet when eaten in whole or traditionally prepared forms. Foods like oats, rice, and true sourdough are preferred. Refined and packaged grain products should be limited.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What about hydration?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Hydration matters. Choose water or unsweetened beverages to accompany meals and snacks.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is the New Pyramid a strict diet?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"No. The New Pyramid is a flexible framework meant to guide better choices, not dictate exact meals. It supports cultural traditions, personal preferences, and different lifestyles while reinforcing one core goal: eat real foods most of the time.\"}}]}0:{\"P\":null,\"b\":\"_Eb6KruK8IFyXhcDkUxOm\",\"p\":\"\",\"c\":[\"\",\"\"],\"i\":false,\"f\":[[[\"\",{\"